00:12:42,680 --> 00:12:44,480
once she's finished
laying the eggs,

272
00:12:44,480 --> 00:12:46,160
but this time, it's different.

273
00:12:46,160 --> 00:12:48,360
Because another nutrient
source is close by,

274
00:12:48,360 --> 00:12:51,120
the mother won't
sacrifice herself.

275
00:12:51,120 --> 00:12:53,240
I hope you all understand
the danger we're in.

276
00:12:56,320 --> 00:12:59,160
I've already advised that
citizens evacuate the city.

277
00:12:59,160 --> 00:12:59,920
All right.

278
00:12:59,920 --> 00:13:01,520
Now listen up, students.

279
00:13:01,520 --> 00:13:03,080
Get your DITE's ready.

280
00:13:03,080 --> 00:13:06,000
The municipal police will handle
the guiding and evacuating

281
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:07,400
of all civilians.

282
00:13:07,400 --> 00:13:10,000
You'll serve as the core of
the Contaminoid offensive.

283
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:12,000
This isn't a drill, people,
so you'll have to fight

284
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:14,320
with everything you've got.

285
00:13:14,320 --> 00:13:16,520
[CHATTER]

286
00:13:16,520 --> 00:13:20,120
Do you really think we'll
be able to beat these things?

287
00:13:20,120 --> 00:13:22,040
KALIAN: It's our only option.

288
00:13:22,040 --> 00:13:24,200
Students, we must
defeat these creatures.

289
00:13:24,200 --> 00:13:26,280
The only alternative is death.

290
00:13:26,280 --> 00:13:29,080
For the sake of the city
of Zuellni, our home,

291
00:13:29,080 --> 00:13:31,280
we have no choice
but to defeat them.

292
00:13:41,040 --> 00:13:42,840
NINA: We've been assigned
to the Northwest sector

293
00:13:42,840 --> 00:13:44,400
along with the 9th Platoon.

294
00:13:44,400 --> 00:13:45,200
Where's Felli?

295
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:47,440
Why can't we get a hold of her?

296
00:13:47,440 --> 00:13:49,360
Nina.

297
00:13:49,360 --> 00:13:50,200
Where have you been?

298
00:13:50,200 --> 00:13:52,040
Don't you know that
we've come under attack?

299
00:13:52,040 --> 00:13:53,000
I know all about it.

300
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:53,840
We're in big trouble.

301
00:13:53,840 --> 00:13:55,680
We have to get out
of here right away.

302
00:13:55,680 --> 00:13:57,280
‐ What are you saying?
‐ Listen.

303
00:13:57,280 --> 00:13:58,440
We need to get to the shelters.

304
00:13:58,440 --> 00:13:59,640
We have to evacuate.

305
00:13:59,640 --> 00:14:00,560
Evacuate?

306
00:14:00,560 --> 00:14:01,640
Don't be ridiculous.

307
00:14:01,640 --> 00:14:03,120
There's no way I'm
running from this.

308
00:14:03,120 --> 00:14:03,880
You don't get it.

309
00:14:03,880 --> 00:14:05,240
Those are Contaminoids.

310
00:14:05,240 --> 00:14:07,560
A bunch of students with
no real battle experience

311
00:14:07,560 --> 00:14:08,720
banding together won't‐‐

312
00:14:08,720 --> 00:14:10,000
NINA: Won't have a prayer?

313
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:10,760
That's right.

314
00:14:10,760 --> 00:14:11,560
They won't.

315
00:14:11,560 --> 00:14:12,480
This isn't a game, Nina.

316
00:14:12,480 --> 00:14:14,800
It's not just some
competition between students.

317
00:14:14,800 --> 00:14:16,760
Every one of them
is going to die.

318
00:14:16,760 --> 00:14:18,680
And so what if we do?

319
00:14:18,680 --> 00:14:20,120
What's your point?

320
00:14:20,120 --> 00:14:22,240
Tell me, what else
are our powers for?

321
00:14:22,240 --> 00:14:24,400
Why do they live
inside each of us?

322
00:14:24,400 --> 00:14:26,240
To protect those who
are important to us,

323
00:14:26,240 --> 00:14:27,800
to defend our home.

324
00:14:27,800 --> 00:14:30,880
No, I'm not running away,
and you shouldn't either.

325
00:14:30,880 --> 00:14:33,640
Your life's been peaceful.

326
00:14:33,640 --> 00:14:35,200
You don't know
what you're saying.

327
00:14:35,200 --> 00:14:36,280
Layfon, you're different.

328
00:14:36,280 --> 00:14:38,000
You're not like the
rest of us here.

329
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:39,200
So you tell me why.

330
00:14:39,200 --> 00:14:41,440
With all the power you have,
why are you running away?

331
00:14:41,440 --> 00:14:43,480
Why won't you stay
here and fight with me?

332
00:14:43,480 --> 00:14:45,280
Because you have no
idea how terrifying

333
00:14:45,280 --> 00:14:46,560
the Contaminoids really are.

334
00:14:46,560 --> 00:14:47,360
You're naive.

335
00:14:47,360 --> 00:14:49,160
You don't know what it
means to take them on.

336
00:14:49,160 --> 00:14:51,360
If we don't stand up
to them now, then when?

337
00:14:51,360 --> 00:14:53,800
Now move!

338
00:14:53,800 --> 00:14:54,600
Nina.

339
00:15:05,800 --> 00:15:08,760
[BUZZING]

340
00:15:21,080 --> 00:15:23,040
All right.

341
00:15:23,040 --> 00:15:26,000
No turning back now.

342
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:27,480
Artillery, fire!

343
00:15:27,480 --> 00:15:29,920
[GUNFIRE]

344
00:15:31,440 --> 00:15:34,000
Concentrate all your fire
on the ones in the air.

345
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:36,240
We've got to keep those
things away from the city.

346
00:15:36,240 --> 00:15:37,480
Yeah, roger that.

347
00:15:37,480 --> 00:15:38,800
I've got a date tomorrow.

348
00:15:38,800 --> 00:15:40,360
There's no way I'm
gonna die today.

349
00:15:40,360 --> 00:15:41,720
Not like this.

350
00:15:41,720 --> 00:15:44,120
[GUNFIRE]

351
00:15:46,480 --> 00:15:49,520
I won't let these
monsters be the end of me.

352
00:15:49,520 --> 00:15:52,800
Restoration.

353
00:15:52,800 --> 00:15:54,800
Now, move out!

354
00:15:54,800 --> 00:15:57,760
[CHEERING]

355
00:16:04,200 --> 00:16:05,200
The shell.

356
00:16:05,200 --> 00:16:06,680
It's so hard.

357
00:16:25,080 --> 00:16:28,320
LAYFON (VOICEOVER): There's
no reason for me to fight.

358
00:16:28,320 --> 00:16:31,280
[WIND BLOWING]

359
00:16:40,760 --> 00:16:41,720
But I‐‐

360
00:16:49,720 --> 00:16:53,200
[HEAVY BREATHING]

361
00:16:53,200 --> 00:16:56,200
[SCREAMING]

362
00:16:59,440 --> 00:17:00,240
Harley.

363
00:17:00,240 --> 00:17:02,560
You're here.

364
00:17:02,560 --> 00:17:03,560
Layfon.
Hey.

365
00:17:03,560 --> 00:17:04,840
What are you doing?

366
00:17:04,840 --> 00:17:06,360
I need you to make
two different settings

367
00:17:06,360 --> 00:17:07,520
for this DITE.

368
00:17:07,520 --> 00:17:08,320
Hold on.

369
00:17:08,320 --> 00:17:09,720
Two settings?

370
00:17:09,720 --> 00:17:10,520
You heard me.

371
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:15,080
LAYFON (VOICEOVER): Senior.

372
00:17:15,080 --> 00:17:16,600
Fon‐Fon.

373
00:17:16,600 --> 00:17:17,480
LAYFON (VOICEOVER): Senior.

374
00:17:17,480 --> 00:17:18,720
I mean Felli.

375
00:17:18,720 --> 00:17:20,400
There's something I
need your help with.

376
00:17:22,920 --> 00:17:25,000
The larvals are
doing the attacking.

377
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:28,240
That means the mother has to
be sleeping somewhere nearby.

378
00:17:28,240 --> 00:17:30,320
I need its precise location.

379
00:17:30,320 --> 00:17:32,320
Find it, Felli.

380
00:17:32,320 --> 00:17:34,000
FELLI (VOICEOVER):
This is a surprise.

381
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:36,680
Now even you tell
me to use my Nen‐I.

382
00:17:36,680 --> 00:17:38,800
If you don't help
me, everyone will die.

383
00:17:38,800 --> 00:17:39,680
LAYFON (VOICEOVER): Felli.

384
00:17:39,680 --> 00:17:42,080
Were the only ones
who can save them.

385
00:17:42,080 --> 00:17:43,520
Please.

386
00:17:43,520 --> 00:17:44,520
Amazing.

387
00:17:44,520 --> 00:17:47,000
You're so hopelessly
soft hearted, aren't you?

388
00:17:59,800 --> 00:18:01,560
There's way too many of them.

389
00:18:01,560 --> 00:18:02,360
Fall back.

390
00:18:02,360 --> 00:18:03,560
Fall back!

391
00:18:03,560 --> 00:18:04,360
Wait.

392
00:18:04,360 --> 00:18:05,360
Don't run away!

393
00:18:05,360 --> 00:18:06,360
Stay at your posts!

394
00:18:06,360 --> 00:18:10,320
If we don't stop
them, we're finished!

395
00:18:10,320 --> 00:18:12,320
Dammit.

396
00:18:12,320 --> 00:18:14,800
[SHOUT]

397
00:18:14,800 --> 00:18:16,800
[SCREECHING]

398
00:18:16,800 --> 00:18:20,000
SHARNID: Nina, look out!

399
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:20,760
Ah!

400
00:18:31,720 --> 00:18:32,680
Damn.

401
00:18:32,680 --> 00:18:33,480
Nina.

402
00:18:33,480 --> 00:18:35,640
Get out of the way.

403
00:18:35,640 --> 00:18:36,440
NINA: I'm gonna die.

404
00:18:47,520 --> 00:18:49,000
What the?

405
00:18:49,000 --> 00:18:49,840
How?

406
00:18:49,840 --> 00:18:50,640
LAYFON: You all right?

407
00:18:53,720 --> 00:18:54,520
NINA: Layfon.

408
00:18:54,520 --> 00:18:57,680
It's you!

409
00:18:57,680 --> 00:18:59,040
I found the nest.

410
00:18:59,040 --> 00:18:59,800
It's like you said.

411
00:18:59,800 --> 00:19:01,120
She's not too far from here.

412
00:19:01,120 --> 00:19:02,560
I'll find a way
in and guide you.

413
00:19:02,560 --> 00:19:03,560
Are you ready?

414
00:19:03,560 --> 00:19:04,360
Let's go.

415
00:19:04,360 --> 00:19:05,160
Nina!

416
00:19:07,400 --> 00:19:08,240
NINA: Layfon.

417
00:19:08,240 --> 00:19:09,720
How‐‐ how did you do this?

418
00:19:09,720 --> 00:19:10,720
Did you‐‐
‐ Look.

419
00:19:10,720 --> 00:19:12,560
There's no time to
explain right now.

420
00:19:12,560 --> 00:19:13,720
Just get out of here, please.

421
00:19:13,720 --> 00:19:14,520
I don't‐‐

422
00:19:14,520 --> 00:19:15,640
You have to go.

423
00:19:15,640 --> 00:19:16,440
Look.

424
00:19:16,440 --> 00:19:18,240
I can handle the
larvals myself, but

425
00:19:18,240 --> 00:19:21,160
if the mother calls for back up,
then we're all in big trouble.

426
00:19:21,160 --> 00:19:21,920
Ah!

427
00:19:29,320 --> 00:19:31,480
Handle the larvals.

428
00:19:31,480 --> 00:19:32,280
Layfong.

429
00:19:32,280 --> 00:19:33,280
How can you‐‐

430
00:19:47,920 --> 00:19:49,280
FELLI (VOICEOVER):
You'll only have five

431
00:19:49,280 --> 00:19:51,040
minutes outside of the city.

432
00:19:51,040 --> 00:19:53,560
Any more than that, and
even your lungs won't last.

433
00:19:53,560 --> 00:19:54,360
Yeah.

434
00:19:54,360 --> 00:19:55,200
Yeah, I know.

435
00:20:00,160 --> 00:20:03,160
Don't die on me, Fong‐Fong.

436
00:20:03,160 --> 00:20:06,160
[MUSIC PLAYING]

437
00:20:20,560 --> 00:20:23,520
[CREAKING]

438
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:35,800
The reason I came to
Zuellni to begin with

439
00:20:35,800 --> 00:20:39,040
is because I wanted
to stop fighting.

440
00:20:39,040 --> 00:20:40,040
Restoration 01.

441
00:20:45,240 --> 00:20:47,720
But now I fully understand.

442
00:20:50,680 --> 00:20:55,640
If I wanna keep living, this
is the only option I have.

443
00:20:55,640 --> 00:20:59,520
This is it, because this is
the world that I live in.

444
00:21:15,120 --> 00:21:15,880
WOMAN: Just talk to me.

445
00:21:15,880 --> 00:21:17,880
Tell me where it hurts.

446
00:21:17,880 --> 00:21:20,560
GIRL: Are you‐‐ are
you all right, sir?

447
00:21:20,560 --> 00:21:21,360
MAN: Thanks.

448
00:21:21,360 --> 00:21:22,160
I'm OK.

449
00:21:34,280 --> 00:21:37,240
Layfon!

450
00:21:37,240 --> 00:21:39,280
Nina.

451
00:21:39,280 --> 00:21:40,880
I'm so glad you're all right.

452
00:21:40,880 --> 00:21:41,680
You're an idiot.

453
00:21:41,680 --> 00:21:43,760
Did you know that, Layfon?

454
00:21:43,760 --> 00:21:46,320
To go flying out of
the city with no gear?

455
00:21:46,320 --> 00:21:48,880
You must be crazy.

456
00:21:48,880 --> 00:21:52,440
I suppose that was a little
on the careless side, huh?

457
00:21:52,440 --> 00:21:55,120
Layfon.

458
00:21:55,120 --> 00:21:57,120
I'm sorry about that.

459
00:21:57,120 --> 00:21:59,600
I think maybe I overdid
it just a little bit.

460
00:21:59,600 --> 00:22:01,120
I'm gonna take a quick nap.

461
00:22:01,120 --> 00:22:01,920
Huh?

462
00:22:01,920 --> 00:22:03,520
Uh, hold on.

463
00:22:03,520 --> 00:22:05,320
What exactly do you
think you're doing?

464
00:22:05,320 --> 00:22:06,120
Hey!

465
00:22:06,120 --> 00:22:07,240
Now, wake up!

466
00:22:07,240 --> 00:22:08,040
I'm serious.

467
00:22:08,040 --> 00:22:09,560
Get off of me!

468
00:22:09,560 --> 00:22:10,400
Layfon.

469
00:22:14,160 --> 00:22:17,440
Oh, forget it.

470
00:22:17,440 --> 00:22:18,560
Rest up.

471
00:22:18,560 --> 00:22:19,560
You did a great job.

472
00:22:30,040 --> 00:22:33,040
[MUSIC PLAYING]

473
00:24:00,520 --> 00:24:02,320
MAN (VOICEOVER): Mayshen
mistakenly receives a letter

474
00:24:02,320 --> 00:24:04,000
addressed to Layfon
and the girls

475
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:06,880
become concerned with the
sender's relationship to him.

476
00:24:06,880 --> 00:24:08,360
Meanwhile, for some
unknown reason,

477
00:24:08,360 --> 00:24:10,880
Layfon gets invited
over to Felli's house.

478
00:24:10,880 --> 00:24:15,280
Next time, The Letter from
Glendan and Restoration.

